<br>
Take one scene from your story/world/characters history that inspires you. Write 500 words, a couple of paragraphs describing the scene, outlining the dialogue or some part of it in detail.<br>
<br>
Go play EQ for a few hours <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Repeat.<br>
<br>
Repeat 4-5 times.<br>
<br>
Reread what you've written, put the paragraphs in a logical order. You now have a short story. It probably won't read very well to an outside observer, but its good writing practice.<br>
<br>
That's a beginning, and that's about as far as I have got <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
In the end you can string together and bulk out those paragraphs, and ones in between and in theory, eventually arrive at a novel. And if any of the bits don't fit or are badly written, you've only wasted half an hour on them.<br>
<br>
But the important thing is NOT to try and write an epic straight off. Write a place, or a conversation, or a battle. Enough of those makes an adventure.<br>
<br>
Like people say, starting at the start sucks. Start in the interesting bits, the rest is just fluff.<br>
<br>
I am also attempting to write a book/create a world or whatever. My bed is usually strewn with pictures and maps of my fantasy world, which although having the base outline drawn up, and lots of pretty dragon pictures drawn, has yet to get off the starting blocks. I'm trying the read-a-lot tactic, in the hope that I will at least learn what NOT to do.<br>
<br>
Oh, and if you ever write this story &quot;Humble farmers boy gets caught up in huge adventure, but using his simple virtue saves the day in the nick of time when even the greats couldn't&quot; please shoot yourself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If your gonna write anything, make sure the plot isn't that same old fantasy plot thats been recycled 5000 times. Original idea &gt; good writing style <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/jimturner99/gyrhawk"></center> <b><center>Gyrhawk - Tunare's Falconer</center></b></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9>OT/OOC Forum</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href="http://www.firionavie.org/">Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.firiona-vie.com/fvchat.html" target="_blank"><h3>Chat Room</a></h3></center> <br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 6.6<br>Copyright ©1999-2001 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  